::heading level=1 id=doc-hero
Welcome to DOC DB Testing
::end

::quote id=hero-tagline
Structured docs that agents can query, humans can edit, and both can trust.
::end

::heading level=2 id=what-is-docdb
What is DOC DB
::end

::paragraph id=docdb-description
DOC DB is a writing environment where every document lives in SQLite. Documents are structured as typed blocks — headings, paragraphs, lists, code, quotes — so they can be searched, styled, and edited programmatically without breaking format.
::end

::heading level=2 id=block-types
Block Types
::end

::bulleted-list id=block-type-list
heading — section titles at any level, H1 through H6
paragraph — body text
quote — pull quotes and callouts
bulleted-list and numbered-list — ordered and unordered items
checklist — checkable task lists
code — source blocks with an optional language tag
image — embedded images with alt captions
rule — horizontal dividers
::end

::heading level=2 id=how-css-works
How Styling Works
::end

::paragraph id=css-policy
CSS blocks are document content. They are stored and versioned like any other block and are NOT globally auto-applied. To activate styling, open any block's inline CSS editor and write declarations for that block's id or class. The editor scopes your rules to the selected block so they never silently affect anything else.
::end

::code id=css-reference lang=css
/* Apply to the H1 by its id */
#doc-hero {
  font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
  letter-spacing: -0.032em;
  line-height: 1.05;
}

/* Apply to the quote by its id */
#hero-tagline {
  font-size: 1.08rem;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
  margin: 1.1rem 0 1.8rem;
}

/* Apply to any block with class=callout */
.callout {
  background: var(--surface-2);
  border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
}
::end

::heading level=2 id=start-here
Start Here
::end

::numbered-list id=getting-started
Open a .dx file in VS Code to see the structured editor.
Click any block to edit its source directly.
Use the CSS icon on a block to apply scoped styles by id or class.
Query documents with the MCP server from any connected agent.
::end
